The user wants me to implement a solution in Kotlin for a shortest path problem involving two modes of travel: empty (no apples) and carrying (with apples).

The problem asks for the minimum cost for each store $i$ to obtain apples.
For store $i$, the options are:
1. Buy directly at $i$: Cost = $prices[i]$.
2. Travel from $i$ (empty) to some store $j$, buy apples at $j$ (Cost = $prices[j]$), and travel back from $j$ to $i$ (carrying).
